<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836941>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Hymeniacidon perlevis (Montagu, 1814)—orange. A–B, live specimens (MNRJ 12181 and MNRJ 12183); C, ectosomal skeleton in tangential ground section (UCSUR 07-000059); D skeleton architecture in transverse ground section (MNRJ 12084); E–F, styles (MNRJ 12084); G–H, details of E. Scale bars: A–B, approx. 2 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 500 µm; E–F, 100 µm; G–H, 20 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836941/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836946>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Hymeniacidon perlevis (Montagu, 1814)—yellow. A–B, live specimens (MNRJ 12859 and MNRJ 11252); C, ectosomal skeleton in tangential ground section (UCSUR-07-000007); D, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section (MNRJ 12859); E–F, styles (MNRJ 12859); G–H, details of E. Scale bars: A, approx. 2 cm; B, 5 cm; C, 200 µm; D, 500 µm; E–F, 100 µm; G–H, 20 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836946/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836938>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Halichondria (Halichondria) prostrata Thiele, 1905. A, live specimen (MNRJ 12884); B, skeleton architecture in transverse ground section; C, skeleton architecture of the ectosome in tangential ground section; D, oxea; E–F, details of D. Scale bars: A, 2 cm; B–C, 500 cm; D, 100 µm; E–F, 20 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

